# Netlify security headers (vulnerability audit 2026-06-09).
# Netlify already sends Strict-Transport-Security on the custom domain.
#
# X-Frame-Options SAMEORIGIN: nothing legitimately frames anchorquoting.com
#   (the in-app PDF viewer frames the Supabase proxy URL, not our origin), so
#   deny embedding to kill clickjacking — incl. overlay tricks on the e-sign page.
# nosniff: never MIME-sniff responses (we serve JSON/PDF/data files from /data/).
# Referrer-Policy: don't leak full URLs (sign/share tokens live in fragments,
#   which are never sent in Referer anyway — this tightens the rest).
# Permissions-Policy: the app never uses camera/mic/geolocation/payment APIs.

/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=(), payment=()
